

	 
       The Irony  I lay in bed, waiting for the night to pass As the clock ticks, so slowly The scent of pee drifting around me room My stuffed dog resting on my bed Tobi, lying against my pillows, His chest heaving as he gasps for breath In the car, rushing to the vet Time passing Minutes vanishing into nothingness In the neighbors van The stench of cigarettes intoxicating my nose My face buried in Tobi’s fur The night it over Minutes gone, an hour past This night together was our last I lay in bed, tears staining my face Eyes puffy, cheeks red Humid air filling my room Time is gone, cant go back And still, the clock ticks, so slowly. 
     
    
